body:
@purechoc Thanks for the contribution.

Like @felixcheung mentioned, alternative approach could be adding a interpreter property [here](https://github.com/apache/zeppelin/blob/master/livy/src/main/resources/interpreter-setting.json#L145) and let LivyPySparkInterpreter be configured with the property without adding new interpreter class.

What do you think?

@astroshim  sorry for the belated response. I worked on fixing the issue of  zeppelin version 0.6.It's solved by installing scala on the docker. This issue only happens with the binary version downloaded from zeppelin website, but when creating an image from create_release.sh script, it worked normally without scala installation requirement.

